The issue is that RabbitMQ doesn't automatically propagate W3C `traceparent`/`tracestate` headers. You need to manually inject context on publish and extract it on consume.

**Service A — Publisher (inject context):**

```csharp
using System.Diagnostics;

// Define a shared ActivitySource
static readonly ActivitySource Source = new("ServiceA.Messaging");

// When publishing:
using var activity = Source.StartActivity("OrderEvent Publish", ActivityKind.Producer);

var props = channel.CreateBasicProperties();
props.Headers ??= new Dictionary<string, object>();

// Inject current trace context into message headers
if (Activity.Current != null)
{
    props.Headers["traceparent"] = Activity.Current.Id;          // W3C trace ID
    props.Headers["tracestate"]  = Activity.Current.TraceStateString ?? "";
}

channel.BasicPublish(exchange, routingKey, props, body);
```

**Service B — Consumer (extract context):**

```csharp
static readonly ActivitySource Source = new("ServiceB.Messaging");

// In your consumer callback:
void HandleMessage(BasicDeliverEventArgs ea)
{
    ActivityContext parentCtx = default;

    if (ea.BasicProperties.Headers?.TryGetValue("traceparent", out var raw) == true)
    {
        var traceparent = Encoding.UTF8.GetString((byte[])raw);
        ActivityContext.TryParse(traceparent, null, out parentCtx);
    }

    // Start a new activity linked to the publisher's trace
    using var activity = Source.StartActivity(
        "OrderEvent Process",
        ActivityKind.Consumer,
        parentContext: parentCtx  // ← this is the key link
    );

    // ... process the order
}
```

**Wire it up in `Program.cs` (both services):**

```csharp
builder.Services.AddOpenTelemetry()
    .WithTracing(t => t
        .AddSource("ServiceA.Messaging")   // or ServiceB.Messaging
        .AddAspNetCoreInstrumentation()
        .AddOtlpExporter());               // or Jaeger/Zipkin
```

**Why this works:** `Activity.Current.Id` carries the full W3C `traceparent` (`00-<traceId>-<spanId>-<flags>`). Passing it as `parentContext` on the consumer side stitches the consumer span into the same trace.

**If you use MassTransit or NServiceBus** — they do this automatically. The manual approach above is only needed with raw `RabbitMQ.Client`.
